During a two-week school placement, students work with the assigned class, get acquainted with the teacher's work, observe lessons and give eight lessons themselves. They analyse and reflect on their work and do home assignments.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support students in the process of becoming a teacher, creating opportunities for implementing theoretical knowledge into practice on the 1st school stage; to develop students' skills of reflection and analysis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student - knows the teaching methods and principles suitable for the first school level, applies them appropriately in teaching; - is able to analyze his / her lessons and other study activities; - has an adequate understanding of the professional responsibilities of a primary school teacher.
